I once pushed un-reviewed code that contained<p><pre><code>  alert(&quot;Fuck&quot;);
</code></pre>
It made it to a single user who was testing it for me, on the other side of the planet. He spoke very little English, and for that I am grateful.<p>That was my last push without review.

I&#x27;m not sure &quot;provide only one way of doing things&quot; is a core principle of C.  It at least seems to have fallen to &quot;type less&quot; in several cases:<p><pre><code>    i = i + 1;
    i += 1;
    i++;
    ++i;

    a[i]
    *(a + i)

    a->foo
    (*a).foo</code></pre>
